class.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.
class.rdfs:label: Place

schema:additionalProperty.rdfs:comment:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.
schema:additionalProperty.rdfs:label: additionalProperty

schema:aggregateRating.rdfs:comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.
schema:aggregateRating.rdfs:label: aggregateRating

schema:amenityFeature.rdfs:comment: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.
schema:amenityFeature.rdfs:label: amenityFeature

schema:branchCode.rdfs:comment:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.
schema:branchCode.rdfs:label: branchCode

schema:containedIn.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
schema:containedIn.rdfs:label: containedIn

schema:containedInPlace.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
schema:containedInPlace.rdfs:label: containedInPlace

schema:containsPlace.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.
schema:containsPlace.rdfs:label: containsPlace

schema:event.rdfs:comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.
schema:event.rdfs:label: event

schema:events.rdfs:comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.
schema:events.rdfs:label: events

schema:geo.rdfs:comment: The geo coordinates of the place.
schema:geo.rdfs:label: geo

schema:globalLocationNumber.rdfs:comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.
schema:globalLocationNumber.rdfs:label: globalLocationNumber

schema:hasMap.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.
schema:hasMap.rdfs:label: hasMap

schema:isAccessibleForFree.rdfs:comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.
schema:isAccessibleForFree.rdfs:label: isAccessibleForFree

schema:isicV4.rdfs:comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.
schema:isicV4.rdfs:label: isicV4

schema:map.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.
schema:map.rdfs:label: map

schema:maps.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.
schema:maps.rdfs:label: maps

schema:maximumAttendeeCapacity.rdfs:comment: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.
schema:maximumAttendeeCapacity.rdfs:label: maximumAttendeeCapacity

schema:openingHoursSpecification.rdfs:comment: The opening hours of a certain place.
schema:openingHoursSpecification.rdfs:label: openingHoursSpecification

schema:publicAccess.rdfs:comment: A flag to signal that the Place is open to public visitors. If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value
schema:publicAccess.rdfs:label: publicAccess

schema:smokingAllowed.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.
schema:smokingAllowed.rdfs:label: smokingAllowed

schema:specialOpeningHoursSpecification.rdfs:comment:
The special opening hours of a certain place.

Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.
schema:specialOpeningHoursSpecification.rdfs:label: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
